        "plan multi-skill design workflow",
        "route design task to correct sub-skill" ;
    oc:yieldsState oc:TaskRouted,
        oc:WorkflowPlanned .

oc:kn_044350c4 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When answering specific design questions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Route brand-related identity questions (colors, voice, consistency audits) to 'brand', token/CSS variable questions to 'design-system', and component implementation questions to 'ui-styling'" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Each skill owns a distinct layer of the design stack; routing to the wrong skill produces answers at the wrong abstraction level" .

oc:kn_1f86127d a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deciding which combination of skills to invoke" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use all eight skills for a complete brand package from scratch (logo → CIP → presentation). Use brand + design-system + ui-styling for design system setup. Use logo-design + cip-design for brand identity with mockups." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Different project scopes require different skill combinations; over-invoking wastes resources, under-invoking misses critical design coherence" .

oc:kn_280fe25f a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always when planning multi-skill workflows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Skill dependency chain must be respected: brand feeds colors/typography to design-system, which feeds tokens/specs to ui-styling, which feeds components to application code" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Violating the dependency order leads to inconsistent design tokens and orphaned brand decisions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_302e5baa a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When setting up a new project from scratch" ;
    oc:directiveContent "New Project Setup: 1) brand → define identity (colors, typography, voice), 2) design-system → create tokens (primitive, semantic, component), 3) ui-styling → implement (configure Tailwind, add components)" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Establishes a dependency chain from brand identity → token formalization → implementation" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_4fd6f2bc a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating a new UI component" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Component Creation: 1) design-system → reference specs (states, sizes, variants), 2) ui-styling → implement (build with shadcn/ui + Tailwind)" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

oc:kn_574ec242 a oc:AssumptionBoundary,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating ambiguous or novel design requests" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The routing guide assumes the user's request maps to one of eight defined skill categories: brand, design-system, ui-styling, logo-design, cip-design, slides, banner-design, or icon-design" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Requests that don't clearly map to a skill category require human clarification to avoid misrouting" .

oc:kn_6b756ade a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When migrating an existing project to a design system" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Design System Migration: 1) brand → audit existing (extract colors, fonts), 2) design-system → formalize tokens (three-layer architecture), 3) ui-styling → update code (replace hardcoded values)" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

oc:kn_e9dd9c3c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a user request covers multiple skill domains" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If a design task spans multiple concerns (e.g., 'create branded component'), decompose it into sequential sub-tasks matching the dependency chain and invoke skills in order" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Multi-domain requests must be decomposed to respect the skill dependency chain and avoid circular dependencies" .

